My assessment
At this point, I think we’re about 80–85% complete.
The remaining 15–20% is the most technically challenging part, but it’s also the most rewarding because it’s where the engine moves from “works in many cases” to “enterprise-grade and trustworthy.”
The encouraging part is that we’ve already solved most of the hard foundational problems: live cross-account discovery, reconciliation planning, target group parity, reporting, rollback concepts, and safe execution modes. What’s left is concentrated in two subsystems—deterministic subnet resolution and complete listener/rule reconciliation—which means the path to completion is now much clearer than it was when we started.
